Objective: be the first to pass finish line (field 90 => Jannowitz, nowadays Jannowice)
learn more about Silesia, especially Riesengebirge (Sudeten Mountains)
- moving by turns/simple 'Roll and Move' game -
Start at Hirschberg (nowadays Jelenina G&oacute;ra);
(pewter) meeples are moved according the die roll;
ending on a marked space follow instructions printed on lid inside.

remarks:
Background of the cover: shows giant 'R&uuml;bezahl', spirit of many Silesian fairytales;
due to Scholz' numbering system game should had been published ~ 1910

Objective: score most points
- acting by turns -
skittle by/with curling 
there are numerous different games (& publishers) with 9 skittles;
speciality of this game: curling tools;
fixing a disc you shoot it into direction of the skittles.

well known game:
each player slides the curl three times into nine skittles;
numbers are summed up - highest sum wins

Objective: score most points flipping a ball into a basket
 - acting by turns -
players try to flip a (table-tennis) ball into a basket, positioned a a height of ~20 inches;

Objective: be the first to get the permanent majority of votes for the coming election of the mayor - learn more about the city of M&ouml;nchengladbach
- simple 'Roll and Move' game, very similar to Monopoly , moving by turn -
Each player rolls the die, moves according the number, follows instruction of space landed on, buys - if possible and/or preferable - votes;
major difference compared with Monopoly;
"chance" cards are created with circumstances out of the history of M&ouml;nchengladbach - question cards give you additional chances/bonuses finding correct answers

Using individually rated player cards and dice "Bones" players select from 10 run or 6 pass plays on offense, and 12 defenses to play a simple to learn, yet very detailed game of football.  Football Bones builds off the original Statis Pro model by Jim Barnes and updates to a Base-10 system allowing for greater variability and realism in the results.  Advanced statistics previously unavailable have allowed us to come up with the most accurate player cards and that translates to accurate play on the field!

Play by Play has been studied and every ball handler in the game now more accurately reflects on-field performance. 3 yards and a cloud of dust, yup we have that!

One of the beauties of the original Statis Pro system was and is the simplicity. Cover 2, Cover 3 it&rsquo;s in there, Wildcat got it!, 6 Offensive lineman got it!, 3 Tight Ends got it! More plays and strategies, weather rules, a new model for quarterbacks and ball handlers. Solo, league, and replay tested&hellip;&hellip; All the fun and excitement of the original Statis Pro game is there and we&rsquo;ve added so much more&hellip;&hellip;

Objective: get most event/action cards; learn more about communication/environment; 
 - acting by turns/simultaneously -
shuffle 2 green, 4 red, 6 orange, 8 blue event/chance cards forming a pile;
create your world by assembling carton pads with a disc/placing  6 'weather' tiles upon the disc; at last fix all together with a rubber band building a tension
active player draws top card, depending on colour you have to solve a question (multiple choice), increase/decrease tension (rubber band), solve calamities (dropped weather tiles); if you are succeeding get corresponding event card...

Objective: hit as many hoodlums as possible
 - acting by turns -
Kim and her friends are trying to hit rogues using a catapult - use box inside as target (zones are marked);
do not hit Ron - you will get a minus point; 
hitting the same target zone - no additional point;
first player achieving 20 points wins the game

Players exchange turns trying to conquer areas by encircling them. Each area has to be cornered by three points at least and the player who controls more points adjacent to an area conquers it. Each area scores different points and the player with the most points, when all points have been claimed, is the winner

